(This file targets v0.9 provider grammar — Channel block + webhook
provider. Will not compile until Phase 4 lands. Use as a worked spec
example showing that the destination URL never appears in source.)

(Compare against the deploy config that binds this channel:

  "channels": {
    "order webhook": {
      "provider": "webhook",
      "config": {
        "target": "https://hooks.example.com/orders",
        "timeout_ms": 10000,
        "retry": { "max_attempts": 5, "backoff": "exponential" },
        "auth": { "type": "hmac", "secret_ref": "${HOOK_SECRET}" }
      }
    }
  }

The same source deploys against any URL by varying only the deploy
config. No URL leaks into the .termin file.)

Application: Order Notifier
  Description: Posts an outbound webhook every time an order is fulfilled.
Id: 7e9b4a23-1f08-4d51-9c6e-8a2d3f5b6c10

Identity:
  Scopes are "orders.read", "orders.write", and "orders.admin"
  A "fulfillment clerk" has "orders.read" and "orders.write"
  A "fulfillment manager" has "orders.read", "orders.write", and "orders.admin"

Content called "orders":
  Each order has a customer which is text, required
  Each order has a total which is currency
  Each order has a fulfilled_at which is automatic
  Anyone with "orders.read" can view orders
  Anyone with "orders.write" can create or update orders

Channel called "order webhook":
  Provider is "webhook"
  Anyone with "orders.admin" can invoke this channel

  When order fulfilled:
    Post `{
      "event": "order.fulfilled",
      "order_id": order.id,
      "customer": order.customer,
      "total": order.total,
      "fulfilled_at": order.fulfilled_at
    }`
